channel.title: Looking for people to work with
channel.description: Hi, I'm looking for a few individuals to develop a base with. I require you be at least adequate with working on java, have database experience, know the internals of how a Runescape client works, and know the basics of git (pull, push, commit, resolving conflicts). Scripting experience is a plus. Inquire here, the official project name is 'Cobalt'.

item.title: Looking for people to work with
item.dc:creator: @sinisoul sini
item.description:
@sinisoul wrote:

Miss Silabsoft:

are you going to be forcing ruby down the developers throats?

No. But I don’t really want to use Java for content. Lua would be great but I’d be open for ideas.

I may be interested, I'll have some free time over summer. I may even learn Ruby or whatever other scripting language you decide, provided you give some sort of documentation on how it works with the server instead of just "learn Ruby and make it work ASAP". Last time I looked into working with you, I was unable to work out how to create an Item object in Ruby and couldn't find a documentation so I gave up.

As long as there is either no scripting, or documented scripting, then yes I am interested. PM me for my email address or Skype name, if you wish.

K I’ll add you after my League game.

Read full topic
